Rating: 4
I've made this many times and have adujsted the recipe as I've gone along to suit my family's taste (and thanks to all the reviewers for help in this!). I put the cut onion in a bowl with 1 head of garlic, sliced. Then I melt the butter in a saucepan and add it to the bowl and toss. Then I spread it on the sheets. This makes it soo much easier. I lower the temperature to 375 and cook until mostly brown (I remove really burned ends). I've tried veggie broth - not yummy. I add only 1 tbsp of sugar, use balsamic instead of red wine vinegar, and have noticed that the flavor gets noticably better if I allow the sauce to reduce all the way down to 1/2 cup. I always make it a day in advance and just pop it in the microwave while I'm boiling the beans - and I only boil the beans about 3 minutes because we love super crisp beans. Last thing - I throw the cooked beans and the sauce in a big bowl and toss them - this ensures that the beans at the bottom of the bowl have sauce on them as well as the ones at the top. I get raves on this every time I make it!!

