Rating: 4
The chicken broth does not have to be reduced as much as indicated -- this only makes it more salty. Reducing it to 1 cup is plenty (add more vinegar and sugar, accordingly). I also slowly sauteed the onions in a large skillet on the stovetop rather than in the oven. Only other note of improvement is to add a cornstarch slurry to the sauce to thicken it up; that way the green beans are nicely glazed with the sauce. A really yummy dish.

